<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Readily distinguishable in the whole genus by the character combination of the reniform to cordate-reniform leaf blades which are purplish red abaxially and palmately-pinnately veined, the solitary and erect capitula, and the pappus which are as long as, or slightly longer, than tube of the tubular corolla.</paragraph>
